</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 436<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/03 9:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Preperation.</span><hr size=1>  For a moment, Dawn watched Hippolyte lead Lysia off. A glimmer of a smile danced across her lips, it was nice to see that amazons could still bond together and get things done; it'd been so long since Dawn had participated in something such as that. After a few moments of silence, Dawn wandered to the camp fire.<br>
<br>
 Grabbing a few spare logs, she tossed them into the fire, not giving it a chance to die down. Dawn knew all to well that the forest in amazon territory was freightening to those whom had never been there, and she wanted to make Cassandra and her sister's stay.. a bit more comfortable to say the least.<br>
<br>
 Dawn settled on the ground before the fire, crossing her twin scabbards across her lap, she folded her arms and hands over them. Sitting comfortably indian style, the amazon fell into a trance, her emerald pools settled on the fire. The only meditation Dawn ever did, was this, before fights, battle, war, she concentrated, focused, and saw what no one else would see. She scryed.<br>
<br>
 As Dawn fell into her thoughts, and the future, she seemed only to waver in the light of the day, and the fire. Pupil's became canine like, and teeth become feline like. Soon, she would be so in touch with her soul, her entire being that shapeshifting would come as a blur to all those around her, and her fighting would truly become the gift those had always been awed by. The gift that had made her a legend. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/03 9:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preperation.</span><hr size=1> Lysia accepted the fronds, and nodded.  &quot;An excellent plan... we'll be done in no time.&quot;  She grinned down at her queen, a far more mature one than she'd had as that earnest teenager. <br>
<br>
For one accustomed to fighting from trees, and in them, navigating on the half built temple was relatively easy.  Frond after frond was laid down and secured, with Lysia's usual precision.  <br>
<br>
By the time Hippolyte returned, she'd set her armor aside - though in reach - in deference to the heat.<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A> at: 2/16/03 9:26:39 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 193<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/03 10:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preperation.</span><hr size=1> Alysia nodded to Lysia and Hippolyte as they walked away from the camp. She then turned and watched as Dawn went into her meditation.<br>
Alysia remembered the last wars they all fought together. Centaurs, Romans, Alternate Amazons, and Rogue warriors. Even the Olympian brought the sisters together.<br>
<br>
She walked over to where she set down her small pouch. She reached in and pulled out two small viles. One, was a red liquid and she opened it, drizzling the liquid on the blade of one dagger. The poisoned appeared as blood. But it was deadly to no extent.<br>
The other vile, she slipped into a small pouch attached to her leather skirt. It was Wolves Blood. The healing remedy that she had discovered many years back in Scynthia. It had been know to heal the most outrageous wounds and infections.<br>
<br>
She then took a seat near the fire where her green orbs stared into the flames. A hint of blue reflected in her eyes, Alysia would always have two sides of her. Aly was her peace. Her inner beauty and love. But the warrior inside was Samsara. Samsara knew no such thing as mercy towards an enemy. They were prey, nothing more to her.<br>
The the fire light her medallions glowed brightly. One Tretmolec, one Scynthian, and one Loire.<br>
<br>
She was ready. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
