<br>
She might have the drive, but Lysia had always been in awe of Hippolyte's presence.  The young warrior had often said, 'Queen Hippolyte could be in rags and muddy, and you'd still know she was royalty'.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 762<br> <font color=#993300>(2/17/03 8:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=39>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preperation.</span><hr size=1> &quot;Good...we get this done, then we can make offerings to Hera.  And then get some rest.&quot;  While she spoke, Hippolyte's hands weaved thru the fronds with strips of vines.  Her slender fingers moving swiftly.  In all of Hipp's life...she was not afraid of work.  In fact, she preferred to work along side her athelfi.  She enjoyed their companionship...and learned from them in return.  <br>
