 True, it had been over a year since Dawn had stepped foot into the famed amazon city of Themiscrya. It was better that way. Her legend hadn't died, nor had the village she had brought to life died. Orio-Pata ran strong, and would one day be as strong as Themiscrya or Scynthia. The assassin just wasn't needed.<br>
<br>
 For a moment the assassin stretched, bringing her arms back behind her back, and then above her head. It was almost time. And in honor Dawn would fight alongside her amazon sisters again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=queenhera>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/03 2:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=45>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/lilhera.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New arrivals.</span><hr size=1> It was hard for Hera to resist the chanting in the wooden hut.  She had been upset that Hippolyte had left Themiscrya to fight at her father's side.  Ares had practically demanded it.  And Zeus was behind him.  As odd as that was, and Hera couldn't fight the both of them.  So, they got their way.<br>
